&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Technical Solutions Consultant&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be the principal technical liaison between our product, sales, and customer success teams. You will provide tailored solutions for clients in the commercial real estate sector, specifically focusing on the complex &lt;strong&gt;VTS Activate product landscape (including Activate, Activate Workplace, Activate Multifamily, CBRE Host, and CBRE Host Building)&lt;/strong&gt;. Your unique combination of property management experience and deep technical proficiency will help ensure that our clients maximize the value of our software.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;** Please note that this opportunity is located in New York, NY, and requires this hire to work from our office 4 days a week. **&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes This Job Awesome?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the definitive subject matter expert (SME) and technical leader for the VTS Activate suite&#39;s integration landscape and partnerships, both internally and externally (e.g., Braxos, Kastle, CCure, AMAG, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver advanced, in-depth technical demonstrations for prospects and clients, specifically showcasing how the VTS Activate product suite solves specific challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide advanced technical support during the sales process, addressing complex questions and concerns about system integrations and core functionalities, serving as the technical closer for Activate deals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support during the sales process for qualifying opportunities with hardware requirement and implementation. Provide handover details to cross-functional stakeholders to ensure smooth implementations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the solution reporting process for VTS Activate deals, including documenting deal journals and synthesizing won/loss reasons. This reporting provides critical intelligence for the Product team (feature gaps), the Sales team (competitive analysis), and the Executive team (market/product trends).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead knowledge transfer and cross-functional upskilling initiatives for the Sales, Customer Success, and Services teams. This involves supporting the creation of documentation and providing semi-formal training specific to technical discovery, deep integration enablement, and complex ongoing support for the Activate product family.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with clients to understand their property management workflows and identify opportunities to implement our software effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a bridge between customers and internal teams, providing technical feedback to influence product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the sales team to develop and execute strategies for prospect engagement and client retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Clients, Product and Engineering teams to help shape API roadmap through scoping capabilities for native and third-party applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You a Great Fit?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deep technical proficiency&lt;/strong&gt; and ability to understand and communicate complex software solutions, with a strong emphasis on API integrations and technical solution delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demonstrated expertise in the VTS Activate product suite&lt;/strong&gt;, with a specific focus on &lt;strong&gt;Activate Multifamily and CBRE Host/Host Building&lt;/strong&gt; products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of relevant experience, with commercial real estate &lt;strong&gt;property management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with property management software platforms such as Angus and Building Engines.&lt;/li&gt;
